In a 6- to 8-quart pan, mix oil, onion, and garlic; stir over high heat until tinged brown, about 8 minutes. Add 1 cup water, marinara sauce, tomatoes and their juices, wine, bay leaf, tarragon, and pepper. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to a simmer. Add crabs; return to simmer. Lay clams on top. Cover; cook 5 minutes over medium-high heat. Push halibut into sauce; lay shrimp and mussels on top. Cover; cook until clams and mussels open and shrimp and halibut are just opaque in thickest part, about 10 minutes. Transfer seafood to bowls as done; continue cooking remainder. Discard unopened clams and mussels. Ladle sauce over seafood in bowls. Garnish with parsley and lemon.